Rating: 4
This is beautiful and so summery! I did a really rough blend so there were still chunks of strawberry in the mixture and then I froze it in my ice cream maker. The aeration by the ice cream maker made it much easier to scoop out when it was time to serve. I added a dollop of whipped cream -- so good! I'm making the next batch tomorrow night with fresh peaches from the farmers market. Can't wait!

Rating: 4
I've made this recipe now twice in 3 days, and it has been a major hit for everyone to whom I've served it. It is so incredibly simple and SO incredibly delicious and full of summer. I can see making this all year long with different fruits. I bet it would be fantastic with peach and raspberry. It does get rock hard in the freezer.

Rating: 4
I've made this three times now. It is a brilliant recipe -- so fresh- tasting, and feels like a real treat even though it is guilt free. I substitute an equal amount of Splenda for the sugar and find that it tastes just as great. It's best to work in small batches when processing the frozen mixture into the creamy end product. Otherwise the machine gets bogged down and the whole process takes longer. I place the finished product into small plastic containers; that way I have individual servings that soften faster.

